-- Ranjit Singh to Head Malaysia Securities Commission
-- B y   R a m s e y   A l - R i k a b i
-- 2012-03-11T05:53:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/ranjit-ajit-sing-named-new-malaysia-securities-commission-head.html
(Corrects spelling of Singh in headline.)  Ranjit Ajit Singh has been
appointed chairman of the Securities Commission of  Malaysia ,
replacing Zarinah Anwar.  Ranjit’s appointment will take effect April 1, the day
after Zarinah’s term ends, according to a statement posted on
the commission’s  website . Ranjit has served the regulatory body
since 1994, according to the statement. He is now the
commission’s managing director and  executive director , market
oversight, according to its  website .  Nik Ramlah Mahmood, the current managing director and
executive director, enforcement, will be appointed deputy chief
executive, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ramsey Al-Rikabi in Singapore at 
 ralrikabi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
